POST /api/process
Process a medical chart image and return structured data.

Request:

json
{
  "image": "base64_encoded_image",
  "ocr_engine": "easyocr",
  "analysis_type": "comprehensive",
  "include_llm_analysis": true
}
Response:

json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "extracted_text": "raw extracted text",
    "structured_data": {
      "patient_information": {...},
      "vital_signs": {...},
      "clinical_data": {...}
    },
    "validation_results": {...},
    "llm_analysis": {
      "openai": {...},
      "cohere": {...},
      "anthropic": {...}
    }
  },
  "metadata": {
    "processing_time": 2.34,
    "confidence_score": 0.87
  }
}
GET /api/health
Check API health status.

Response:

json
{
  "status": "healthy",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "timestamp": "2024-01-01T12:00:00Z"
}
Batch Processing
python
from src.main import process_batch_directory

# Process multiple charts
results = process_batch_directory(
    input_dir="./medical_charts/",
    output_dir="./results/",
    ocr_engine="easyocr"
)
Error Handling
All API methods return structured error responses:

python
try:
    result = ocr_engine.extract_text(image)
except Exception as e:
    print(f"OCR processing failed: {e}")
